BUG-003

Module:
Login

Environment:
Application: OWASP Juice Shop
Browser: Google Chrome
Operating System: Windows 10/11

Description:
The Password field on the Login page does not allow users to paste a copied password using keyboard shortcuts or the context menu, affecting usability and compatibility with password managers.

Preconditions:
User is on the Login page.
A password has been copied to the clipboard.

Steps to Reproduce:
Open the OWASP Juice Shop Login page.
Copy a valid password from any text editor.
Click inside the Password field.
Press Ctrl + V or use Right-click → Paste.
Observe the behavior.

Expected Result:
The Password field should accept pasted text, allowing users to paste passwords copied from a clipboard or password manager.

Actual Result:
The Password field does not accept pasted text, and the copied password is not inserted.

Severity:
Medium

Priority:
Medium
